The paper presents a data structure for range reporting on a point set, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and data analysis. The paper also builds upon the Locality-Sensitive Hashing (LSH) framework, which is a popular technique in computer science for solving near neighbor problems. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
